Review: i want what hot priest no. 1 (piolo) and hot priest no. 2 (cedrick) had… 🧍‍♂️✨
-did not know this was gonna be completely set in pampanga, the way they used betute tugak and kamaru for mood setting 😭
The gay conundrum of “do I love him or do I wanna be him” taken to the extreme. So indulgent and so horny.

Movie: NCT NATION: To the World in Cinemas
Review: like, I get that they have to find a way to distribute the screen time between 20 members but they did not have to cut to a new shot every 2 seconds (i counted) during the dance numbers… 😬 my brain did NOT register anything that was happening !!

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
Review: When I read the book for this, the Suzanne Collins’ style of writing and world building felt so familiar and comforting that I sped through it in one night. A bit dumb because I ended up not remembering much about the story. 😅 Anyways, the filmmaking for this felt just as familiar. The Hunger Games movies will always be THAT franchise.
i liked the the bits where the characters play off of each other, the Marvel Banter™ in this actually worked for me…. the superhero stuff, not so much.
Park date scene still made me want to combusttttt. 🥹
if i was in her shoes i would've befriended the little one and named it kokey, it was kinda cute 🥺
Took me a while to get calibrated sa flavor ng camp this was going for, kaso just when I thought I’ve convinced myself that I can vibe with it, it went for something else entirely. 😵‍💫

Movie: One Piece: Defeat the Pirate Ganzak!
Review: Still finding the 1000+ episode anime too daunting to start but sure I can watch a <30 mins 90’s OVA. 😌
that smash cut paired with the final “야“ felt like a dagger to the heart. devastating.
